GIT INSTALLATION

if machine is linux or MAC OS , git is already installed
if machine is windows, have to install git binary.

	- check git installation via git --version 

2) How to do git config on your machine;
	- git config --global user.name "username"
	- git config --global user.email "email"
check the config if correctly then 
	- git config --list

3) cloning repo from remote server to local
	git clone <url>
4) make the changes you want to do on your local then once finished then pushing to staging area is
	- git add .  
	- git add file name  (this is just to push partiular files)

5) pushing to local server 
	- git commit -m "jira id and message"
6) pushing to remote server is 
	- git push origin <branch name>

##########ABOVE STEPS ARE GENERAL STEPS#############################




####BRANCHING###############
1: git branch -a (this will list all the branches in your local machine as well as remote server)
2: to create new branch from base branch 
	git checkout -b branch_name
